article.headline: Ball St. 95, Mount St. Joseph 43
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. -- Pierre Sneed scored a career-high 15 points while Jauwan Scaife and Jarrod Jones added another 15 each in Ball State's 95-43 win over Mount St. Joseph on Tuesday night. The Cardinals (6-3) began the game with a 10-0 run and were up 43-18 by halftime. They shot 65.5 percent from the field in the second half and made the final score their biggest lead. Randy Davis added 14 points for Ball State while Malik Perry scored 13. Alex Cole scored 12 points, becoming the only player for the Lions (2-9) to score in double digits. Mount St. Joseph finished shooting just 24.6 percent from the field but managed 60 percent from the free-throw line.
